Section R CTAN Edition

Welcome to the XML based and XSL generated version of The TeX Catalogue Online, Section R CTAN Edition. This is a listing of entries in the TeX Catalogue and may take a little time to load, but is hopefully worth it. Have a look at the Catalogue Preface for alternative ways of accessing the catalogue.

The TeX Catalogue Online is also available from any CTAN node or mirror, including the following. Pick one that is close to you. (The "search" link attempts to find a CTAN node that may be close to you, courtesy of Randy Kobes. Multiple clicks may find alternatives.)

Icons associated with many entries in the catalogue allow you to:

  • view the directory on CTAN
  • view documentation (possibly many)
  • view documentation in PDF format (requires the acroread plugin)
  • jump to the package's home page
  • download a gzip'd tar file from a nearby CTAN node (not supported by all nodes)
  • download a gzip'd tar file from ftp.dante.de

Other icons simply provide further information about the package:

  • part of the teTeX distribution
  • available on the TeX Live CD ROM

The license type, version (if known), and the date of the last change made to each particular Catalogue entry are also provided.

ragged No caption.
Provides any TeX format (including LaTeX) with `raggedleft' and `raggedcenter' formatting of paragraphs while maintaining full control of hyphenation and degree of raggedness.
license: unknown (1 Apr 1991)
ragged2e No caption.
A LaTeX package which defines new commands \Centering, \RaggedLeft, and \RaggedRight and new environments Center, FlushLeft, and FlushRight, which set ragged text and are easily configurable to allow hyphenation.
license: lppl version: 1.01 (1999/03/03)
rail No caption.
A C program and LaTeX package to draw syntax diagrams specified in EBNF. See also syngen
license: unknown version: 1.2 (1998/10/1)
rangecite Will turn a range of citations into something like [1..3].
Will turn a range of citations into something like [1..3]. See also cite
license: unknown (1996/05/28)
rawfonts No caption.
A LaTeX2e package providing emulation of LaTeX 2.09 documents which used low-level font commands such as \tenrm.
license: unknown version: 0.01 (1997/06/6)
rawprint Print raw Russian text.
A package for ``quick and dirty'' printing of raw (i.e., non-TeX) Russian texts by persons who do not have Russian printer fonts (but have Cyrillic TeX). It makes various symbols ``normal'' letters and converts the ``unisex'' quote character \" into Russian-style << and > > quotes.
license: lppl (1999/03/29)
rcs Use RCS (revision control system) tags in LaTeX documents.
Use RCS (revision control system) tags in LaTeX documents.
license: unknown (1 Apr 1991)
rcsinfo Support for the revision control system.
A package to extract RCS (Revision Control System) information and use it in a LaTeX document. For users of LaTeX2HTML rcsinfo.perl is included.
license: unknown version: 1.6 (1999/02/25)
realcalc Macros for real arithmetic calculations.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
recipe A LaTeX2e class file to typeset recipes.
license: unknown (1996/11/26)
refcheck No caption.
Intended to check references in a document, looking for numbered but unlabelled equations, for labels which are not used in the text, for unused bibliography references. It can also display label names in text near corresponding numbers of equations and/or bibliography references.
license: lppl (1999/03/03)
refman Format technical reference manuals.
A new document class for writing technical reference manuals. It offers a wide left margin for notes to the reader, like some of the manuals distributed by Adobe.
license: lppl version: 2.0c (1999/04/2)
relenc No caption.
LaTeX package providing a relaxed font encoding to make available to a font designer more slots for insertion of ligatures and accented characters.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
relsize Set the font size relative to the current font size.
license: unknown (1 Apr 1991)
remreset Remove counters from reset list.
\@removefromreset is a companion to the standard \@addtoreset command which allows counters to be removed from the reset list of a controlling counter.
license: lppl (1999/04/11)
repeat No caption.
A really general loop macro, which can be nested to arbitrary depth without any grouping or such.
license: unknown (1999/01/5)
revnum No caption.
Provides a reverse-enumerate environment where all items are numbered in reverse order.
license: unknown (1998/03/3)
revtex Styles for various Physics Journals.
Includes styles for American Physical Society, American Institute of Physics, and Optical Society of America. Only works in compatibility mode under LaTeX2e.
license: nosell version: 3.1 (1999/03/03)
rlepsf No caption.
A macro package for use with epsf.tex which allows PostScript labels in an eps file to be replaced by TeX labels.
license: lppl (1999/03/03)
rmpage A package to help change page layout parameters in LaTeX.
It lets you change page layout parameters in small steps over a range of values using options. It can set \textwidth appropriately for the main fount, and ensure that the text fits inside the printable area of a printer. An rmpage-formatted document can be typeset identically without rmpage after a single cut and paste operation. Local configuration can set defaults: for all documents; and by class, by printer, and by paper size. The geometry package is better if you want to set page layout parameters to particular measurements.
license: unknown (1998/02/5)
romaniantex No caption.
A LaTeX2e package for type-setting Romanian in a multi-lingual TeX environment.
license: unknown (1996/11/15)
romanneg Roman Neg.
license: unknown (1998/04/19)
rotating No caption.
A package built on the standard LaTeX graphics package to perform all the different sorts of rotation one might like, including complete figures and tables and captions. See also graphics lscape
license: lppl (1999/03/26)
rotfloat Rotate floats.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
rplain Redefines the `plain' pagestyle.
The page numbers are now in the lower right corner. See also pageno
license: unknown (1998/09/23)
rsfs No caption.
Contains MetaFont sources for fonts of uppercase script letters for use as symbols in scientific and mathematical typesetting, in contrast to the informal script fonts such as that used for the `calligraphic' symbols in the TeX math symbol font. See also calrsfs rsfs-ps
license: lppl (1999/03/03)
rsfs-ps No caption.
Converted (PostScript) outlines of the rsfs fonts.
license: unknown (1998/04/25)
ruhyphen Russian hyphenation.
A collection of Russian hyphenation patterns supporting a number of Cyrillic font encodings, including T2, UCY (Omega Unicode Cyrillic), LCY, LWN (OT2), and koi8-r.
license: lppl version: 1.1 (1999/03/29)
ruler A ruler for TeX.
license: gpl (1999/05/19)
r-und-s No caption.
This package decodes the german `R- und S-S\"atze', which are numerically coded security advice for chemical substances into plain text. This is, e.g., used to compose security sheets or lab protocols and especially useful for students of chemistry.
license: dfsg (1999/04/14)
runic Fonts for Anglo-Saxon futharc script.
This font was used in England until just after printing was established.
license: lppl (1999/03/26)
